1
00:01:36,509 --> 00:01:39,990
[NORTHWARD]

2
00:01:40,110 --> 00:01:41,970
[Episode 34]

3
00:01:56,759 --> 00:01:57,560
Mr. Xie.

4
00:02:01,430 --> 00:02:02,150
Well,

5
00:02:02,950 --> 00:02:04,590
w-we saw what happened next

6
00:02:05,840 --> 00:02:07,930
on the news.

7
00:02:08,960 --> 00:02:10,900
The accident was not all your fault.

8
00:02:11,450 --> 00:02:12,750
Tianming is gone,

9
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:14,680
leaving us orphaned and widowed.

10
00:02:14,680 --> 00:02:16,600
I really had no choice.

11
00:02:17,160 --> 00:02:19,160
but to contact the media.

12
00:02:20,280 --> 00:02:23,829
I never thought it would make you lose your job

13
00:02:24,050 --> 00:02:25,960
and get a barrage of criticism.

14
00:02:26,810 --> 00:02:27,660
Forget about it.

15
00:02:29,300 --> 00:02:31,800
Take care of yourselves from now on.

16
00:02:32,390 --> 00:02:34,190
If you run into any difficulties, feel free to come to me.

17
00:02:34,360 --> 00:02:35,520
I'll do my best to help you.

18
00:02:36,760 --> 00:02:37,790
Well...

19
00:02:38,060 --> 00:02:40,070
Bee has sent someone to meet us,

20
00:02:40,170 --> 00:02:42,829
saying they'd help us pay off the mortgage.

21
00:02:43,280 --> 00:02:44,690
So please take this card back.

22
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:47,430
No... That's what they should do.

23
00:02:47,720 --> 00:02:48,900
I wanted to make amends.

24
00:02:49,570 --> 00:02:50,720
Just keep it.

25
00:02:50,960 --> 00:02:53,130
You'll need it for the children's future education.

26
00:02:53,820 --> 00:02:56,400
Who committed the crime should pay the price.

27
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:59,690
I can't bear to take your card.

28
00:03:04,670 --> 00:03:06,260
Fenghua has left.

29
00:03:06,620 --> 00:03:08,180
We have to move too.

30
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:10,310
Do you know why she left?

31
00:03:10,860 --> 00:03:12,410
Wasn't she just doing well?

32
00:03:12,860 --> 00:03:15,640
You'll have to ask her about that.

33
00:03:16,620 --> 00:03:18,760
She handed over her work

34
00:03:19,079 --> 00:03:20,560
and satisfied everyone.

35
00:03:21,070 --> 00:03:22,470
But she didn't

36
00:03:22,660 --> 00:03:24,240
say a word about her feelings.

37
00:03:24,370 --> 00:03:27,010
Honestly, we all felt quite frustrated.

38
00:03:27,410 --> 00:03:28,510
After the meeting,

39
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:30,840
she left right away even before we

40
00:03:30,870 --> 00:03:32,000
said goodbye properly.

41
00:03:32,810 --> 00:03:34,930
We're still

42
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:36,360
reeling from it now.

43
00:03:42,130 --> 00:03:43,420
There's one more thing.

44
00:03:44,360 --> 00:03:45,710
P-Please don't get mad at me

45
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:47,970
after you hear it.

46
00:03:48,630 --> 00:03:49,470
Go ahead.

47
00:03:52,970 --> 00:03:55,640
Fenghua probably sold the parcel delivery station

48
00:03:56,520 --> 00:03:57,910
because of me.

49
00:04:00,440 --> 00:04:01,470
Why?

50
00:04:02,700 --> 00:04:04,640
Someone once came to meet me.

51
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:07,440
They wanted me to mess with Bee

52
00:04:07,540 --> 00:04:09,190
and ruin their reputation.

53
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:11,140
They also gave me 300,000 yuan.

54
00:04:11,850 --> 00:04:13,600
After Fenghua found it out,

55
00:04:13,630 --> 00:04:15,900
she asked me to return it, but I refused.

56
00:04:15,930 --> 00:04:18,660
Then she gave me 300,000 yuan herself

57
00:04:18,690 --> 00:04:20,790
and told me to keep it secret from everyone.

58
00:04:21,180 --> 00:04:23,770
Not until she sold the parcel delivery station

59
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:27,260
did I realize that she was running out of money.

60
00:04:27,880 --> 00:04:29,720
I'm sorry, Mr. Xie.

61
00:05:29,350 --> 00:05:30,360
Tumor?

62
00:05:34,510 --> 00:05:35,659
I guess

63
00:05:37,610 --> 00:05:38,780
she's been sick for quite a while

64
00:05:39,760 --> 00:05:41,470
and arranging the affairs before death.

65
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:43,770
She even transferred her parcel delivery station.

66
00:05:48,810 --> 00:05:50,850
I knew she was feeling under the weather.

67
00:05:52,080 --> 00:05:54,690
She told me it was anemia, and I believed her.

68
00:05:56,340 --> 00:05:58,150
How could I be so dumb?

69
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:03,600
Well...

70
00:06:03,630 --> 00:06:04,710
Should we go back too?

71
00:06:09,040 --> 00:06:10,310
I need to

72
00:06:11,050 --> 00:06:13,140
finish He's funeral arrangements first.

73
00:06:13,970 --> 00:06:16,290
I gotta ensure they receive the compensation.

74
00:06:16,330 --> 00:06:17,340
Otherwise,

75
00:06:18,190 --> 00:06:19,510
Fenghua would also be worried.

76
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:25,890
Then I'll go back first.

77
00:06:25,920 --> 00:06:27,570
Anyway, I also feel pretty exhausted lately,

78
00:06:27,590 --> 00:06:29,030
not in the mood for job hunting.

79
00:06:29,060 --> 00:06:30,570
You wanted to go back

80
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:32,409
a long time ago, didn't you?

81
00:06:42,570 --> 00:06:44,320
All of you

82
00:06:44,590 --> 00:06:45,840
are deserters,

83
00:06:46,510 --> 00:06:48,190
leaving me here alone.

84
00:06:55,390 --> 00:06:56,460
Aren't you tired?

85
00:06:59,380 --> 00:07:00,130
Yes, I am.

86
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:03,110
I'm dead tired.

87
00:07:04,020 --> 00:07:05,640
But I don't want to lose.

88
00:07:06,860 --> 00:07:08,220
We should get back up

89
00:07:09,030 --> 00:07:10,910
from wherever we fell.

90
00:07:15,760 --> 00:07:16,760
Fine.

91
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:19,680
Take your time getting back up.

92
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,410
I'm out of this.

93
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:27,990
Let's not tell anyone

94
00:07:28,010 --> 00:07:29,960
about Fenghua's situation for now.

95
00:07:30,740 --> 00:07:32,540
Go back and check on her condition.

96
00:07:32,570 --> 00:07:33,920
If it's not good,

97
00:07:33,940 --> 00:07:35,220
I'll head back immediately.

98
00:07:35,409 --> 00:07:37,940
I'll force her to come to Beijing for treatment no matter what.

99
00:08:03,430 --> 00:08:04,720
Have you decided what to do?

100
00:08:09,570 --> 00:08:10,250
Not yet.

101
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:12,920
You plan to keep idling about, right?

102
00:08:15,360 --> 00:08:16,430
Please don't worry,

103
00:08:17,870 --> 00:08:18,680
I can't stay at home for long.

104
00:08:18,680 --> 00:08:19,600
Or I'll suffocate.

105
00:08:19,940 --> 00:08:21,380
Why don't you learn a trade?

106
00:08:25,070 --> 00:08:26,190
Learn what?

107
00:08:27,220 --> 00:08:28,100
Carpentry

108
00:08:28,720 --> 00:08:29,720
or tailoring, anything will do.

109
00:08:29,740 --> 00:08:31,140
Just have a skill to rely on

110
00:08:31,750 --> 00:08:32,870
and live off, at least.

111
00:08:33,580 --> 00:08:36,460
It's better than just messing around in society, right?

112
00:08:39,880 --> 00:08:41,429
I can go work as a construction laborer.

113
00:08:42,039 --> 00:08:44,230
You don't have the strength for that.

114
00:08:44,630 --> 00:08:46,200
You could learn to be a mason.

115
00:08:47,710 --> 00:08:49,710
It's said skilled ones can earn quite a bit in a day.

116
00:08:50,630 --> 00:08:51,940
Or you could ask Wanghe's father

117
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:54,120
to teach you how to drive. That works too.

118
00:08:55,080 --> 00:08:56,010
I'm full.

119
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:57,320
Enjoy your meal.

120
00:09:12,160 --> 00:09:13,270
You're full too?

121
00:09:30,790 --> 00:09:31,320
Take care.

122
00:09:31,320 --> 00:09:32,490
Goodbye, Mr. Zhou.

123
00:09:33,010 --> 00:09:34,460
Your dishes taste so good.

124
00:09:34,700 --> 00:09:35,460
Xingchi.

125
00:09:34,730 --> 00:09:38,400
[By the Canal]

126
00:09:36,790 --> 00:09:37,470
Mr. Zhou.

127
00:09:37,490 --> 00:09:38,180
Have you eaten yet?

128
00:09:39,550 --> 00:09:40,120
Yep.

129
00:09:44,780 --> 00:09:46,320
Want some plain noodles.

130
00:09:47,270 --> 00:09:48,240
Come on.

131
00:09:58,890 --> 00:09:59,550
Here you are.

132
00:10:01,540 --> 00:10:02,320
Be careful, it's hot.

133
00:10:02,320 --> 00:10:03,000
It's okay. I got this.

134
00:10:09,680 --> 00:10:10,760
No hurry.

135
00:10:10,790 --> 00:10:11,760
It's hot.

136
00:10:14,980 --> 00:10:17,180
I often cooked for myself in Beijing too.

137
00:10:18,490 --> 00:10:22,180
But the noodles I made were nowhere near as good as yours.

138
00:10:22,300 --> 00:10:23,600
I always felt

139
00:10:23,740 --> 00:10:24,920
there was a difference.

140
00:10:25,880 --> 00:10:28,030
Of course there was a difference!

141
00:10:28,460 --> 00:10:29,550
Listen.

142
00:10:29,570 --> 00:10:31,330
These noodles may look plain,

143
00:10:31,350 --> 00:10:33,420
but it's all about the details, you know?

144
00:10:33,450 --> 00:10:34,880
How to make the lard,

145
00:10:35,030 --> 00:10:36,150
how to cook the broth,

146
00:10:36,180 --> 00:10:37,530
how to fry the shrimp roe,

147
00:10:37,550 --> 00:10:40,420
and also what brand and what type of soy sauce to use,

148
00:10:40,450 --> 00:10:41,580
there are knacks for them.

149
00:10:42,220 --> 00:10:42,980
What knacks?

150
00:10:43,640 --> 00:10:45,050
Do you think I can tell you?

151
00:10:45,770 --> 00:10:48,340
It's a secret, a secret recipe. Understand?

152
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:50,490
I haven't even told Haikuo.

153
00:10:51,290 --> 00:10:53,230
Haikuo doesn't even like plain noodles.

154
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:54,910
There were several times in Beijing

155
00:10:54,960 --> 00:10:56,080
when we said we wanted to eat Huaiyang cuisine.

156
00:10:56,490 --> 00:10:58,130
Haikuo refused, saying he was so over it.

157
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:03,440
Actually, we all felt

158
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:05,650
homesick

159
00:11:05,680 --> 00:11:06,730
in Beijing,

160
00:11:07,520 --> 00:11:10,030
but Haikuo didn't seem to feel the same

161
00:11:11,930 --> 00:11:12,880
except for that one time.

162
00:11:14,080 --> 00:11:15,180
At that time,

163
00:11:15,300 --> 00:11:17,470
Haikuo was mistreated at work.

164
00:11:17,500 --> 00:11:18,420
He drank all night...

165
00:11:19,040 --> 00:11:20,990
I want to go home!

166
00:11:21,020 --> 00:11:21,610
Be careful...

167
00:11:21,670 --> 00:11:22,350
Don't fall.

168
00:11:22,390 --> 00:11:23,670
I want to go home!

169
00:11:23,670 --> 00:11:25,260
Go home... We're just going home now.

170
00:11:25,320 --> 00:11:27,790
I'm gonna swim back to the Flower Street!

171
00:11:27,790 --> 00:11:28,150
It's dangerous!

172
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:29,080
Are you crazy?

173
00:11:29,080 --> 00:11:30,200
Come down...

174
00:11:30,270 --> 00:11:31,030
It's a deep river!

175
00:11:31,330 --> 00:11:32,550
Don't mess around!

176
00:11:33,440 --> 00:11:34,440
Are you nuts?

177
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:36,200
In Beijing,

178
00:11:36,220 --> 00:11:38,100
I'm just like grass.

179
00:11:38,830 --> 00:11:40,070
Go home!

180
00:11:40,090 --> 00:11:41,810
I'm going back to my father.

181
00:11:42,330 --> 00:11:45,910
Even if I fail, he still treats me like a treasure.

182
00:11:45,960 --> 00:11:47,150
Who compared you to grass?

183
00:11:47,170 --> 00:11:48,520
I'll go fight him.

184
00:11:50,430 --> 00:11:51,560
I'm hungry.

185
00:11:51,910 --> 00:11:54,400
I want to eat the plain noodles my dad makes.

186
00:11:57,860 --> 00:11:58,800
I'm useless.

187
00:11:59,910 --> 00:12:01,600
I couldn't hold out in Beijing anymore,

188
00:12:01,670 --> 00:12:02,790
so I ran back home first.

189
00:12:04,610 --> 00:12:06,450
But I think Haikuo will also come back one day.

190
00:12:08,810 --> 00:12:09,570
Why?

191
00:12:11,900 --> 00:12:13,900
Wanghe is like a shark.

192
00:12:14,100 --> 00:12:16,150
He thrives in big cities.

193
00:12:16,490 --> 00:12:18,370
Haikuo and I are like freshwater fish.

194
00:12:19,010 --> 00:12:21,420
Only on the Flower Street, by the canal,

195
00:12:21,450 --> 00:12:22,690
do we feel like ourselves.

196
00:12:25,950 --> 00:12:26,910
Enjoy the noodles.

197
00:12:32,900 --> 00:12:34,260
I think

198
00:12:34,280 --> 00:12:35,630
you should feel lucky.

199
00:12:37,730 --> 00:12:38,850
Lucky about what?

200
00:12:38,880 --> 00:12:40,490
For such a materialistic girl,

201
00:12:40,870 --> 00:12:43,810
breaking up early is much better than getting married and then divorcing.

202
00:12:47,550 --> 00:12:50,150
The last time she came to meet me,

203
00:12:50,170 --> 00:12:51,860
I just didn't like her.

204
00:12:51,890 --> 00:12:55,010
But you were still in a relationship,

205
00:12:55,060 --> 00:12:56,750
so I didn't feel it was my place to say it.

206
00:12:56,810 --> 00:12:58,170
You're my mother.

207
00:12:58,980 --> 00:12:59,860
My real mother.

208
00:13:00,970 --> 00:13:03,770
You didn't even tell me when you thought I had chosen the wrong girlfriend.

209
00:13:06,090 --> 00:13:09,090
Whether two people are suitable for each other can only be told by themselves.

210
00:13:09,110 --> 00:13:11,300
Other people's opinions don't matter that much.

211
00:13:13,480 --> 00:13:14,480
So,

212
00:13:15,930 --> 00:13:17,530
when you find someone suitable again,

213
00:13:18,170 --> 00:13:20,520
you won't ask for my opinion either, right?

214
00:13:23,510 --> 00:13:24,800
What do you mean?

215
00:13:26,900 --> 00:13:28,230
After all these years,

216
00:13:29,720 --> 00:13:31,690
h-haven't you found someone suitable?

217
00:13:35,610 --> 00:13:37,380
Dad has never dated anyone.

218
00:13:39,080 --> 00:13:40,150
When others tried to set him up,

219
00:13:40,550 --> 00:13:42,120
he refused to meet anyone.

220
00:13:42,790 --> 00:13:43,790
So what?

221
00:13:44,550 --> 00:13:45,670
Your dad is more devoted than me.

222
00:13:45,670 --> 00:13:47,840
Should I give him an award or something?

223
00:13:49,550 --> 00:13:51,670
I know you're feeling down because of your breakup.

224
00:13:51,690 --> 00:13:54,450
I understand, but don't take it out on me.

225
00:13:54,480 --> 00:13:56,330
That's not what adults should do.

226
00:13:59,890 --> 00:14:02,370
Though Xiaohui said it was because of the house

227
00:14:03,020 --> 00:14:04,370
that she broke up with me,

228
00:14:04,660 --> 00:14:05,900
I feel like

229
00:14:06,910 --> 00:14:08,320
it's not just about the house.

230
00:14:10,440 --> 00:14:11,720
Are you trying to say

231
00:14:12,440 --> 00:14:14,480
that because of your dad and me,

232
00:14:14,910 --> 00:14:16,670
you have been traumatized

233
00:14:16,670 --> 00:14:17,440
and therefore

234
00:14:17,840 --> 00:14:19,840
can't start an intimate relationship?

235
00:14:20,560 --> 00:14:21,560
Is that it?

236
00:14:21,580 --> 00:14:22,460
What do you think?

237
00:14:26,440 --> 00:14:27,440
I admit

238
00:14:28,790 --> 00:14:30,440
that you're feeling unhappy now

239
00:14:30,790 --> 00:14:32,320
partly because of your dad and me.

240
00:14:33,030 --> 00:14:34,320
But who says

241
00:14:35,090 --> 00:14:37,780
people must live in perfect harmony?

242
00:14:37,810 --> 00:14:39,640
Can't there be other choices?

243
00:14:39,770 --> 00:14:41,060
And who says

244
00:14:41,090 --> 00:14:43,490
women can only stay at home to support their husbands, raise children,

245
00:14:43,510 --> 00:14:45,630
and stick to old clichÃ©s

246
00:14:45,660 --> 00:14:47,660
for their whole lives?

247
00:14:52,800 --> 00:14:53,670
I feel bad for you,

248
00:14:54,850 --> 00:14:57,010
and I understand what you've been through.

249
00:14:59,080 --> 00:14:59,980
However,

250
00:15:00,440 --> 00:15:02,030
I'm so sorry.

251
00:15:02,080 --> 00:15:03,080
Because I have never

252
00:15:03,080 --> 00:15:04,790
regretted my choices.

253
00:15:05,110 --> 00:15:07,940
In fact, I'm even proud of myself.

254
00:15:08,930 --> 00:15:12,690
I sincerely hope you can be like me,

255
00:15:12,710 --> 00:15:14,470
not caring about anyone's opinions

256
00:15:14,500 --> 00:15:16,300
and living for yourself bravely.

257
00:15:18,770 --> 00:15:21,220
One day when you understand what I just said,

258
00:15:22,030 --> 00:15:24,960
I believe you'll applaud yourself.

259
00:15:27,930 --> 00:15:28,740
Mom,

260
00:15:31,440 --> 00:15:33,430
I'm not as mature as you think.

261
00:15:35,150 --> 00:15:37,150
All these years, you've been chasing your dreams,

262
00:15:39,120 --> 00:15:41,120
and we could only support you.

263
00:15:41,730 --> 00:15:43,780
But have you ever considered our feelings?

264
00:15:45,550 --> 00:15:47,390
Actually, I'm quite envious of others.

265
00:15:48,810 --> 00:15:49,780
In our neighborhood,

266
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:53,380
other families all live in harmony,

267
00:15:55,080 --> 00:15:56,150
But our family

268
00:15:57,370 --> 00:15:58,840
has always been missing one member.

269
00:15:59,970 --> 00:16:02,140
I don't even dare to mention you to Wanghe and others

270
00:16:03,090 --> 00:16:04,200
because I'm afraid

271
00:16:05,860 --> 00:16:08,740
it'll occur to them

272
00:16:09,450 --> 00:16:10,450
that I have a mom.

273
00:16:13,570 --> 00:16:17,540
You've never told me any of this before.

274
00:16:19,270 --> 00:16:20,200
Why didn't you tell me?

275
00:16:20,200 --> 00:16:21,200
You're my mom.

276
00:16:24,040 --> 00:16:25,210
I should

277
00:16:25,790 --> 00:16:28,660
do my best to fulfill my duty as a son,

278
00:16:29,530 --> 00:16:32,180
trying not to cause you any trouble or stress you out.

279
00:16:33,690 --> 00:16:34,740
But Mom,

280
00:16:37,440 --> 00:16:38,730
I also hope

281
00:16:39,750 --> 00:16:42,020
you can fulfill your duty as a mother,

282
00:16:45,650 --> 00:16:47,570
and, like other moms,

283
00:16:48,850 --> 00:16:51,320
remember that you have a son now and then.

