00:16:54,630 --> 00:16:58,510
But it seems like

285
00:16:58,630 --> 00:17:01,140
you barely remember the existence

286
00:17:01,920 --> 00:17:03,800
of the person named Zhou Haikuo.

287
00:17:05,060 --> 00:17:06,410
It's just that I'm too busy.

288
00:17:06,440 --> 00:17:07,569
All these years on set,

289
00:17:07,589 --> 00:17:10,310
I've been too swamped even without time to sleep properly.

290
00:17:10,339 --> 00:17:11,470
Y-You know that.

291
00:17:11,500 --> 00:17:13,390
How long does it take you to reply to a WeChat message?

292
00:17:18,400 --> 00:17:19,550
I know you're busy,

293
00:17:22,440 --> 00:17:24,480
too busy to say thank you after receiving the flowers

294
00:17:26,770 --> 00:17:29,010
I sent you on Mother's Day.

295
00:17:30,420 --> 00:17:31,420
My dad,

296
00:17:32,090 --> 00:17:33,370
he's a man of few words

297
00:17:34,550 --> 00:17:36,400
who barely says anything nice.

298
00:17:36,790 --> 00:17:38,550
But when he knew I had a fever in Beijing,

299
00:17:40,200 --> 00:17:42,550
he came here overnight without hesitation

300
00:17:43,550 --> 00:17:45,480
and didn't leave until my fever broke.

301
00:17:46,810 --> 00:17:47,530
Mom,

302
00:17:52,440 --> 00:17:53,790
I came to meet you

303
00:17:55,070 --> 00:17:56,590
after breaking up with my girlfriend

304
00:17:59,790 --> 00:18:01,790
not for some lecture.

305
00:18:06,550 --> 00:18:08,510
Even if you don't say a word,

306
00:18:11,810 --> 00:18:13,090
a hug from you

307
00:18:17,580 --> 00:18:18,510
would be enough.

308
00:18:21,360 --> 00:18:22,530
You know what?

309
00:18:23,850 --> 00:18:25,370
All I need now

310
00:18:27,710 --> 00:18:29,300
is just a mom.

311
00:19:00,210 --> 00:19:04,940
[By the Canal]

312
00:19:03,290 --> 00:19:04,640
Mr. Shao.

313
00:19:07,940 --> 00:19:09,550
What's with that face?

314
00:19:09,580 --> 00:19:10,810
Haven't you seen a beautiful woman before?

315
00:19:15,050 --> 00:19:16,050
Where are the two of them?

316
00:19:17,770 --> 00:19:18,970
In Beijing.

317
00:19:19,300 --> 00:19:21,310
I came back alone this time.

318
00:19:23,780 --> 00:19:24,590
So, you will...

319
00:19:24,640 --> 00:19:25,440
I will not leave again.

320
00:19:25,920 --> 00:19:27,250
Really?

321
00:19:28,430 --> 00:19:30,380
Can't I also be a deserter

322
00:19:30,400 --> 00:19:31,270
like you?

323
00:19:31,300 --> 00:19:32,870
Yes, you can!

324
00:19:33,360 --> 00:19:34,620
Welcome home!

325
00:19:34,960 --> 00:19:35,830
Let me help you with that.

326
00:20:01,830 --> 00:20:03,210
It's so good to be back.

327
00:20:03,700 --> 00:20:06,420
I can smell the familiar aroma of food every day again.

328
00:20:08,400 --> 00:20:09,880
Did you tell Wanghe about your return?

329
00:20:12,860 --> 00:20:13,770
Nope.

330
00:20:14,130 --> 00:20:16,240
If I told him, he definitely wouldn't let me return.

331
00:20:16,400 --> 00:20:17,840
I snuck back myself.

332
00:20:25,230 --> 00:20:27,000
That incident of his is over now, right?

333
00:20:29,390 --> 00:20:30,830
He did lose his job.

334
00:20:31,610 --> 00:20:32,940
But he can rest for a while.

335
00:20:33,850 --> 00:20:35,290
Given his amazing capabilities,

336
00:20:35,320 --> 00:20:36,560
as long as he keeps his spirits up,

337
00:20:36,580 --> 00:20:38,450
he can make a comeback anytime.

338
00:20:38,480 --> 00:20:39,960
The company made him a scapegoat in public.

339
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:41,510
I'm just worried about his mental state.

340
00:20:41,530 --> 00:20:42,950
He'll be fine.

341
00:20:43,070 --> 00:20:44,720
That guy is really tough.

342
00:20:45,660 --> 00:20:46,740
I believe

343
00:20:47,250 --> 00:20:49,810
no setback in this world can take him down.

344
00:20:49,840 --> 00:20:50,920
He's been faking it.

345
00:20:50,940 --> 00:20:52,830
If I get into trouble like this, I'll surely break down.

346
00:20:54,500 --> 00:20:56,000
He can't sit idle.

347
00:20:56,820 --> 00:20:59,420
What about you? Have you decided what to do?

348
00:21:02,560 --> 00:21:03,320
Not yet.

349
00:21:05,790 --> 00:21:06,780
Why not come work with me?

350
00:21:07,460 --> 00:21:10,090
That would be a shame! No way.

351
00:21:10,120 --> 00:21:12,770
What do you mean? Are you discriminating against women?

352
00:21:12,800 --> 00:21:14,520
How am I any worse than Wanghe?

353
00:21:15,120 --> 00:21:17,120
I'm just reluctant to work for you.

354
00:21:17,290 --> 00:21:20,880
It would turn our relationship into a boss-employee one.

355
00:21:28,570 --> 00:21:29,670
I'm hungry.

356
00:21:30,590 --> 00:21:31,630
Make me something to eat.

357
00:21:32,730 --> 00:21:33,810
What would you like to eat?

358
00:21:34,620 --> 00:21:37,060
Eel noodles, braised shredded tofu,

359
00:21:37,110 --> 00:21:39,380
lion's head meatballs, sweet and sour spare ribs.

360
00:21:39,970 --> 00:21:40,760
Okay.

361
00:21:41,150 --> 00:21:43,340
I'll make you all these dishes. But I'll hit you if you can't finish them.

362
00:22:09,420 --> 00:22:10,490
How about

363
00:22:10,980 --> 00:22:12,420
we go to Beijing?

364
00:22:13,330 --> 00:22:14,370
Why?

365
00:22:17,200 --> 00:22:18,860
Our son's in such big trouble.

366
00:22:19,700 --> 00:22:21,410
I'm afraid he can't pull through.

367
00:22:24,390 --> 00:22:25,560
Well,

368
00:22:26,690 --> 00:22:28,310
if he really did that,

369
00:22:28,350 --> 00:22:29,840
he deserves to be sacked.

370
00:22:31,030 --> 00:22:32,570
If he's been wrongly accused,

371
00:22:34,100 --> 00:22:36,350
it's good to leave that kind of company anyway.

372
00:22:38,180 --> 00:22:41,490
I'm just worried about our son's feelings.

373
00:22:44,630 --> 00:22:46,160
Everyone will suffer

374
00:22:46,640 --> 00:22:47,720
more or less in life.

375
00:22:49,430 --> 00:22:52,290
Taking a fall like this at his age is actually a blessing.

376
00:22:52,660 --> 00:22:54,360
He's still got the strength to get back up.

377
00:22:54,680 --> 00:22:56,400
Anyway, I have confidence in our son.

378
00:22:56,420 --> 00:22:57,180
Alright...

379
00:22:57,720 --> 00:22:59,110
Stop overthinking it. It's time to sleep.

380
00:23:06,200 --> 00:23:07,400
Look at this Xie's face.

381
00:23:07,400 --> 00:23:08,990
You can tell he's not a good guy at first glance.

382
00:23:09,040 --> 00:23:10,480
I dug into Xie's info.

383
00:23:10,480 --> 00:23:12,030
Seems like he's been in jail before.

384
00:23:13,840 --> 00:23:16,070
He's obviously been made a scapegoat.

385
00:23:16,070 --> 00:23:17,070
You don't believe this?

386
00:23:17,070 --> 00:23:18,400
Bee Group paid a high price

387
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:20,200
to get Xie to take the blame.

388
00:23:20,220 --> 00:23:22,460
How could someone like this become an executive at Bee Group?

389
00:23:22,490 --> 00:23:23,820
He'll end up back in jail sooner or later.

390
00:23:23,880 --> 00:23:25,880
People like him will do anything for money.

391
00:23:26,290 --> 00:23:27,980
As a delivery rider, seeing this kind of news,

392
00:23:28,010 --> 00:23:29,590
I can't help but feel scared.

393
00:23:29,590 --> 00:23:30,640
Yet here I am,

394
00:23:30,640 --> 00:23:31,990
still on the way to deliver.

395
00:23:55,330 --> 00:23:56,910
The victim is gone.

396
00:23:56,930 --> 00:23:59,680
To prevent such tragedies from happening again,

397
00:23:59,710 --> 00:24:01,190
I, on behalf of myself,

398
00:24:01,210 --> 00:24:02,860
hereby make the following proposals

399
00:24:02,890 --> 00:24:04,750
to online food delivery platforms

400
00:24:04,780 --> 00:24:07,010
represented by Bee for their future planning

401
00:24:07,030 --> 00:24:08,470
and development.

402
00:24:08,500 --> 00:24:10,420
First, optimize the system

403
00:24:10,750 --> 00:24:12,610
to allow for flexible time.

404
00:24:12,640 --> 00:24:14,160
In cases of bad weather,

405
00:24:14,180 --> 00:24:16,220
accidents, or other special circumstances,

406
00:24:16,350 --> 00:24:17,900
delivery riders can get special treatment

407
00:24:18,040 --> 00:24:20,650
with their ratings and incomes not being affected.

408
00:24:20,970 --> 00:24:23,530
Second, ensure safety.

409
00:24:23,560 --> 00:24:26,470
For office buildings, hospitals, and other places with difficult access

410
00:24:26,490 --> 00:24:27,960
and navigation issues,

411
00:24:28,160 --> 00:24:30,460
try to set up smart food pickup lockers.

412
00:24:30,530 --> 00:24:32,510
Third, provide humanitarian care.

413
00:24:32,530 --> 00:24:35,150
Offer insurance and medical assistance to delivery riders,

414
00:24:35,170 --> 00:24:37,400
and when necessary, provide educational support

415
00:24:37,480 --> 00:24:38,790
for their family members.

416
00:24:38,890 --> 00:24:40,610
Last but not least, I hope

417
00:24:40,640 --> 00:24:42,630
Bee and all food delivery companies

418
00:24:42,650 --> 00:24:44,300
can take this incident

419
00:24:44,330 --> 00:24:46,050
as a serious lesson

420
00:24:46,070 --> 00:24:47,920
and not repeat the same mistakes

421
00:24:47,950 --> 00:24:49,470
in pursuit of excessive profits.

422
00:24:51,210 --> 00:24:52,770
[Stop acting like a good person. Were it not for you, he wouldn't be dead.]

423
00:24:52,770 --> 00:24:53,770
[He's using tricks to clear his name.]

424
00:24:53,800 --> 00:24:56,420
[I think it's another case of malicious marketing.]

425
00:24:56,420 --> 00:24:58,920
[Why can't we listen to his advice calmly?]

426
00:24:58,940 --> 00:25:00,620
[Stop acting like a good person. Were it not for you, he wouldn't be dead.]

427
00:25:00,620 --> 00:25:03,640
[Venting your anger here won't fix anything. I think Xie Wanghe is right.]

428
00:25:03,640 --> 00:25:07,020
[Especially the proposal for smart food pickup lockers. That's great. No more worries about lost food deliveries.]

429
00:25:07,050 --> 00:25:09,580
[So what if we think it's good? They're unaware of it.]

430
00:25:09,580 --> 00:25:12,840
[@Bee Delivery, @Eat Well, @Yuntu]

431
00:25:12,840 --> 00:25:14,620
[Take notes, guys!]

432
00:25:14,620 --> 00:25:17,640
[Here's your chance. Don't miss it.]

433
00:25:17,660 --> 00:25:20,840
[Everybody, @ them!]

434
00:25:20,860 --> 00:25:23,360
[I can't live without food delivery riders.]

435
00:25:23,370 --> 00:25:25,890
[I just gave a bottle of water to a delivery rider.]

436
00:25:25,920 --> 00:25:28,020
[Positive energy!]

437
00:25:30,400 --> 00:25:31,100
[Bee Delivery Initiated a Proposal to Online Food Delivery Platforms]

438
00:25:31,450 --> 00:25:33,520
[Repost]

439
00:25:40,460 --> 00:25:41,860
[I'm waiting for food delivery right now. No rush.]

440
00:25:42,110 --> 00:25:43,220
[Delivery riders need better insurance coverage.]

441
00:25:43,240 --> 00:25:44,550
[Yes, fewer tricks, more care.]

442
00:25:45,050 --> 00:25:46,200
[Humans don't have to make things difficult for humans. What if your family member is a delivery rider?]

443
00:25:46,560 --> 00:25:47,900
[My dad got laid off and became a food delivery rider. He's working really hard.]

444
00:25:50,390 --> 00:25:53,490
[I've been late for 3 orders today. I'm so exhausted.]

445
00:25:51,170 --> 00:25:53,490
[Be careful on the way. Cheer up.]

446
00:25:52,170 --> 00:25:53,490
[Get some rest. Take care.]

447
00:25:56,540 --> 00:25:58,450
[Bee Delivery Initiated a Proposal to Online Food Delivery Platforms]

448
00:25:58,710 --> 00:25:59,770
[Bee Delivery Initiated a Proposal to Online Food Delivery Platforms]

449
00:25:59,840 --> 00:26:02,120
[Xie Wanghe]

450
00:26:26,700 --> 00:26:27,500
Mr. Meng.

451
00:26:30,310 --> 00:26:32,930
Your PR approach this time is worth learning from.

452
00:26:33,960 --> 00:26:35,440
The more open you are to criticism,

453
00:26:35,870 --> 00:26:37,510
the more you can win people over.

454
00:26:38,650 --> 00:26:39,620
I hope

455
00:26:40,930 --> 00:26:42,980
such incidents won't happen again in the future.

456
00:26:43,820 --> 00:26:45,020
No way.

457
00:26:46,250 --> 00:26:47,970
Traffic accidents are unavoidable.

458
00:26:48,200 --> 00:26:51,110
No one knows when an accident will occur.

459
00:26:53,160 --> 00:26:54,800
Then we must stay on our toes.

460
00:26:55,030 --> 00:26:57,790
Before the next accident happens,

461
00:26:58,310 --> 00:26:59,990
we need to consider all possibilities

462
00:27:00,380 --> 00:27:02,120
and prepare relevant contingency plans.

463
00:27:13,320 --> 00:27:14,450
Well written.

464
00:27:15,480 --> 00:27:17,510
In the past few days, our legal department and law firm

465
00:27:17,530 --> 00:27:18,820
have also been working on a set of plans,

466
00:27:18,850 --> 00:27:21,450
regulating official compensation

467
00:27:21,480 --> 00:27:22,680
and pension payments,

468
00:27:23,260 --> 00:27:24,170
Moreover,

469
00:27:24,680 --> 00:27:26,470
there will be a training program.

470
00:27:27,240 --> 00:27:29,680
All delivery riders, before they officially hit the road,

471
00:27:29,680 --> 00:27:31,920
must pass a traffic safety test.

472
00:27:31,960 --> 00:27:33,510
Otherwise, they won't be assigned orders.

473
00:27:35,200 --> 00:27:36,790
Setting rules alone is not enough.

474
00:27:37,560 --> 00:27:38,990
You also need your people

475
00:27:39,010 --> 00:27:40,010
to implement them strictly.

476
00:27:55,090 --> 00:27:56,180
Let me do it.

477
00:27:56,550 --> 00:27:57,380
No, thanks.

478
00:28:05,770 --> 00:28:07,330
Are you sure these items

479
00:28:07,360 --> 00:28:09,030
are all your personal belongings?

480
00:28:09,670 --> 00:28:10,480
You're leaving the company.

481
00:28:10,890 --> 00:28:12,740
Company property cannot be taken away.

482
00:28:14,790 --> 00:28:16,180
Do you want to check?

483
00:28:16,210 --> 00:28:17,340
That's compulsory.

484
00:28:26,680 --> 00:28:28,070
Qiu Lin,

485
00:28:28,440 --> 00:28:29,480
don't go too far.

486
00:28:29,960 --> 00:28:31,720
Mr. Xie used to be a leader after all.

487
00:28:35,290 --> 00:28:37,790
Xie Wanghe, the Best Service Star.

488
00:28:39,920 --> 00:28:40,690
Alright,

489
00:28:41,460 --> 00:28:42,740
you can get lost now.

490
00:28:46,960 --> 00:28:47,680
Mr. Song,

491
00:28:48,830 --> 00:28:50,310
thank you for your hard work this time.

492
00:28:52,200 --> 00:28:52,960
It's my duty.

493
00:28:56,200 --> 00:28:57,790
As a veteran of the company,

494
00:28:58,580 --> 00:29:00,110
it was my job and duty

495
00:29:00,140 --> 00:29:01,700
to clean up the company

496
00:29:02,050 --> 00:29:04,030
and kick out a troublemaker like you

497
00:29:04,050 --> 00:29:05,740
in person.

498
00:29:09,000 --> 00:29:09,790
You two,

499
00:29:11,170 --> 00:29:12,450
take care.

500
00:29:13,080 --> 00:29:13,880
We will.

501
00:29:16,580 --> 00:29:17,730
What are you looking at?

502
00:29:18,400 --> 00:29:19,770
Didn't we get through this?

503
00:29:26,680 --> 00:29:27,550
Bro,

504
00:29:28,030 --> 00:29:29,100
are you really

505
00:29:29,130 --> 00:29:30,420
just letting him go like this?

506
00:29:30,750 --> 00:29:31,790
Yep.

507
00:29:32,750 --> 00:29:34,030
If you don't kill the snake when you strike,

508
00:29:34,050 --> 00:29:35,320
you'll surely suffer from it later.

509
00:29:35,880 --> 00:29:37,670
If he continues to work in this industry,

510
00:29:40,450 --> 00:29:41,820
I'll never

511
00:29:41,850 --> 00:29:43,160
feel at ease.

512
00:29:48,000 --> 00:29:49,930
Do you know where his weak spot is?

513
00:30:08,480 --> 00:30:09,240
Hello, Mr. Xie.

514
00:30:10,820 --> 00:30:11,860
I'm Jiang Ping from Yuntu.

515
00:30:15,340 --> 00:30:15,830
Hello.

516
00:30:15,860 --> 00:30:16,540
Hello.

517
00:30:16,680 --> 00:30:17,080
Please have a sit.

518
00:30:17,110 --> 00:30:17,640
Thanks.

519
00:30:22,440 --> 00:30:23,590
This is my business card.

520
00:30:29,570 --> 00:30:30,720
Sorry,

521
00:30:31,330 --> 00:30:33,330
I know you haven't been in a good mood lately.

522
00:30:33,360 --> 00:30:34,270
I once planned

523
00:30:34,290 --> 00:30:35,850
to reach out after a while,

524
00:30:35,880 --> 00:30:37,600
yet I was worried that other companies

525
00:30:37,620 --> 00:30:39,690
might approach you and give you an offer first.

526
00:30:41,310 --> 00:30:42,510
Given what happened to me,

527
00:30:42,540 --> 00:30:44,170
who would be so crazy to give me an offer?

528
00:30:46,440 --> 00:30:47,880
Others may not know,

529
00:30:48,050 --> 00:30:49,810
but we've been keeping a close eye

530
00:30:49,830 --> 00:30:51,290
on your every move at Bee.

531
00:30:51,810 --> 00:30:52,810
In Haidian,

532
00:30:52,840 --> 00:30:54,470
in such a short time

533
00:30:54,500 --> 00:30:56,260
and under such adverse conditions,

534
00:30:56,280 --> 00:30:58,520
you've been crushing our Yuntu in business.

535
00:30:59,330 --> 00:31:01,750
It's literally a business miracle.

536
00:31:01,770 --> 00:31:03,750
Let's skip the flattery

537
00:31:03,970 --> 00:31:04,780
and just get to the point.

538
00:31:04,990 --> 00:31:06,280
What do you want from me?

539
00:31:07,830 --> 00:31:09,070
Well, I'm here

540
00:31:09,810 --> 00:31:10,810
with you

541
00:31:10,840 --> 00:31:12,230
to sincerely invite you to join us.

542
00:31:14,910 --> 00:31:15,780
Actually,

543
00:31:15,810 --> 00:31:17,070
given your personality,

544
00:31:17,130 --> 00:31:18,770
you fit in way better with our Yuntu.

545
00:31:19,110 --> 00:31:19,720
Why?

546
00:31:20,590 --> 00:31:22,150
A wolf travels a thousand miles for meat;

547
00:31:22,170 --> 00:31:23,570
a dog does the same for shit.

548
00:31:23,600 --> 00:31:24,640
You're a wolf.

549
00:31:24,660 --> 00:31:27,380
There's no need for you to lead a flock of dogs to eat leftovers, right?

550
00:31:28,710 --> 00:31:29,960
You're overpraising me.

551
00:31:30,570 --> 00:31:32,320
I'm just a defeated man.

552
00:31:35,330 --> 00:31:36,680
Honestly,

553
00:31:37,000 --> 00:31:39,150
everyone in this industry knows

554
00:31:39,240 --> 00:31:40,270
that this time,

555
00:31:40,290 --> 00:31:41,720
you're taking the fall for the company.

556
00:31:41,850 --> 00:31:42,810
But we didn't expect

557
00:31:42,840 --> 00:31:44,790
Meng to go this far,

558
00:31:44,980 --> 00:31:46,820
not even leaving you a way out.

559
00:31:47,370 --> 00:31:48,400
This kind of thing

560
00:31:48,430 --> 00:31:49,430
would never happen

561
00:31:49,450 --> 00:31:51,070
in our Yuntu.

